### 4.1 Ashoka Fellowship

- **What:** Lifetime fellowship for social entrepreneurs with a new, system-changing idea. Global network of 3,800+ Ashoka Fellows across 90+ countries.
- **Offers:** Stipend (3 years), access to global Ashoka network, pro-bono professional services, lifetime peer support
- **Eligibility:** Must have a NEW IDEA (not just an organization), demonstrate creativity in both vision and execution, show entrepreneurial quality, and demonstrate ethical fiber. Full-time commitment required.
- **How to Apply:** Nomination-based (not open application). Can self-nominate or be nominated by Ashoka staff, volunteers, partners, or existing Fellows. Submissions accepted year-round on a rolling basis.
- **Selection Process:** Local team review --> site visits --> panel of 3-4 leading entrepreneurs interviews candidate --> consensus decision --> Ashoka board election
- **Deadline:** Rolling (no fixed deadline)
- **Fit for Samay Sarthi:** EXCELLENT -- emergency response coordination for ambulances/hospitals/traffic police is a system-changing idea in Indian healthcare. The social impact angle is very strong. However, the founder needs to demonstrate years of commitment and the idea must be genuinely novel.
- **URL:** https://www.ashoka.org/en-us/program/ashoka-fellowship
- **How to Nominate:** https://www.ashoka.org/en-id/recommend-ashoka-fellow
- **Source:** [Ashoka Fellowship](https://www.ashoka.org/en-us/program/ashoka-fellowship)

